systemComponent_AgentConversation_conclu.annotation: The message shown to the user when human agent ends the chat.
systemComponent_AgentConversation_conclu.message: Chat session ended. Thanks for chatting with us.

systemComponent_AgentConversation_errorM.annotation: The message shown to the user when Digital Assistant experiences errors with the agent chat system.
systemComponent_AgentConversation_errorM.message: Chat session error. The reason is: {0}.

systemComponent_AgentConversation_exitKe.annotation: Comma-delimited list of keywords the user can use to end the chat with the agent.
systemComponent_AgentConversation_exitKe.message: bye, take care, see you, goodbye

systemComponent_AgentConversation_expiry.annotation: The message shown to the user when the chat session expires.
systemComponent_AgentConversation_expiry.message: Chat session expired. Thanks for chatting with us.

systemComponent_AgentConversation_waitEx.annotation: The message shown to the user when the chat expires while waiting for an agent.
systemComponent_AgentConversation_waitEx.message: The request for live chat expired while waiting for an agent.

systemComponent_AgentInitiation_agentAct.annotation: Message preceding the list of agent actions.
systemComponent_AgentInitiation_agentAct.message: \n Here are the available actions that you can send to transfer the conversation back to the bot. Prepend the action with a forward slash (for example, /actionName).\n

systemComponent_AgentInitiation_errorMes.annotation: The message shown to user when system error occurs during chat initiation with agent.
systemComponent_AgentInitiation_errorMes.message: Error transferring to agent. The reason is: {0}.

systemComponent_AgentInitiation_rejected.annotation: The message shown to the user when human agent rejects the chat request.

systemComponent_AgentInitiation_resumedM.annotation: The message shown to the user when the chat with human agent is resumed.

systemComponent_AgentInitiation_waitingM.annotation: The message that's shown to users when they are waiting for a human agent.
systemComponent_AgentInitiation_waitingM.message: Agent chat session established, Waiting for agent to join.

systemComponent_AgentTransferCondition_e.annotation: The message shown to the user when Digital Assistant experiences trouble checking agent status with the agent chat system.
systemComponent_AgentTransferCondition_e.message: We were unable to check the status of other agents because there was a system error.

systemComponent_AgentTransfer_acceptedMe.annotation: The message that's shown to the users whenever a human agent accepts the chat request.
systemComponent_AgentTransfer_acceptedMe.message: The chat has been transferred to another agent.

systemComponent_AgentTransfer_errorMessa.annotation: The message shown to the user when Digital Assistant experiences trouble with the agent chat system.
systemComponent_AgentTransfer_errorMessa.message: We were unable to transfer you to another agent because there was a system error.

systemComponent_AgentTransfer_rejectedMe.annotation: The message that's shown to the users whenever a human agent rejects the chat request, 'maxEngagementsInQueue' is exceeded, the 'allowTransferIf' condition is not met, or the estimated wait time exceeds 'maxWaitSeconds'.

systemComponent_AgentTransfer_waitingMes.annotation: The message that's shown to users when they're transferred to a human agent.
systemComponent_AgentTransfer_waitingMes.message: Agent chat session established, Waiting for agent to join.

systemComponent_CommonResponse_formTitle.annotation: Default title shown in form dialog when using table-form message type on Slack.

systemComponent_CommonResponse_showFormB.annotation: Button label to open form when using a table-form layout.

systemComponent_Feedback_feedbackPrompt.annotation: It is the prompt shown to the user to select rating for the conversation.
systemComponent_Feedback_feedbackPrompt.message: How would you rate this conversation?

systemComponent_Feedback_invalidValuePro.annotation: It is the prompt shown to the user to select rating for the conversation after user inputs an invalid value for rating.
systemComponent_Feedback_invalidValuePro.message: Value submitted for feedback rating is invalid. Please try again

systemComponent_Feedback_skipLabel.annotation: The label of the skip button to skip the feedback.

systemComponent_Feedback_textFeedbackPro.annotation: Prompt shown to user asking them to provide text feedback when they give a rating below threshold.

systemComponent_Feedback_thankYouPrompt.annotation: It is the prompt shown to the user when transition set by user is not defined in dialog flow.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_answe.annotation: Message that's displayed for Intelligent Advisor interview inputs of type Masked when the user's answer doesn't conform to the specified input mask.
systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_answe.message: The answer is not in the correct format. Try again.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_defau.annotation: Text that's added to a question when the Intelligent Advisor interview input has a default value.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_doneH.annotation: Help message that's displayed for Intelligent Advisor interview inputs of type Upload.
systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_doneH.message: When you are done with the upload, say {0}.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_doneL.annotation: The text that users have to type to indicate that they are done uploading a file.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_endLa.annotation: The label that is shown in the chat at the end of the interview.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_exitL.annotation: The text that users have to type to indicate that they want to exit the interview.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_expla.annotation: The question that is asked when showExplanation is set to 'ask'.
systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_expla.message: Do you want to see the explanation?

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_maskL.annotation: Text that's added to a question to display the expected format for Intelligent Advisor interview inputs of type Masked Text Box.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_noLab.annotation: The label to use to represent Boolean FALSE values.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_numbe.annotation: Message that's displayed when the user enters a value outside of the specified range for an Intelligent Advisor interview input of type Slider.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_outOf.annotation: Error message that's displayed when the user taps a button in a previous Intelligent Advisor interview message.
systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_outOf.message: You have already answered this question. When you want to step backwards to change a previous answer, say {0}.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_reset.annotation: The text that users have to type to indicate that they want to go back to the first question.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_resum.annotation: Question that is asked if the user starts an interview that they had previously left before the interview completed.
systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_resum.message: Do you want to restart the interview from where you previously left?

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_uncer.annotation: The label that appears for optional values and is what the user can type if they don't know the value.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_undoL.annotation: The text that users have to type to indicate that they want to go back to the previous question.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_yesLa.annotation: The label to use to represent Boolean TRUE values.

systemComponent_IntelligentAdvisor_yesNo.annotation: Message that's displayed when the user enters an invalid answer for Intelligent Advisor interview inputs of type Boolean Radio Button.

systemComponent_Intent_optionsPrompt.annotation: The prompt shown to the user when there are multiple top intents within the confidence win margin.

systemComponent_Intent_optionsQnaLabel.annotation: The label of the action in the options (see optionsPrompt) that will take the user to the QnA component to display the matches.

systemComponent_KnowledgeSearch_defaultA.annotation: The default label to use for the result card's URL action that is linked with an attachment of the search result if that attachment does not have a display name configured already.

systemComponent_KnowledgeSearch_noResult.annotation: The text to output when no search result is available.
systemComponent_KnowledgeSearch_noResult.message: Sorry, no result was found in the knowledge search.

systemComponent_KnowledgeSearch_resultLi.annotation: The label to use for the result card's URL action that's linked to the web version of the knowledge article.

systemComponent_OAuth2AccountLink_cancel.annotation: The label for the cancel button that lets users leave the state without invoking the authentication dialog.

systemComponent_OAuth2AccountLink_linkLa.annotation: The label for the button that invokes the authentication dialog.

systemComponent_OAuth2AccountLink_prompt.annotation: The message that tells users to sign in now.

systemComponent_OAuthAccountLink_cancelL.annotation: The label for the cancel button that lets users leave the state without invoking the authentication dialog.

systemComponent_OAuthAccountLink_linkLab.annotation: The label for the button that invokes the authentication dialog.

systemComponent_OAuthAccountLink_prompt.annotation: The message that tells users to sign in now.
systemComponent_OAuthAccountLink_prompt.message: Please tap on the link to proceed

systemComponent_QnA_answersLabel.annotation: The label for the action to view answers in a particular category.

systemComponent_QnA_categoriesLabel.annotation: The label for the action to display the categories that match the user utterance.

systemComponent_QnA_exitLabel.annotation: The label for the exit questions action.

systemComponent_QnA_moreAnswersLabel.annotation: The label for the action to paginate to next set of answers.

systemComponent_QnA_moreCategoriesLabel.annotation: The label for the action to paginate to next set of categories.

systemComponent_QnA_subCategoriesLabel.annotation: The label for the action to display sub-categories within a given category.

systemComponent_QnA_viewAnswerLabel.annotation: The label for the action to view answer details.

systemComponent_ResolveEntities_defaultD.annotation: Default message shown when the user entered ambiguous input causing multiple entity matches.

systemComponent_ResolveEntities_defaultP.annotation: Default message shown to prompt the user for input.

systemComponent_ResolveEntities_showMore.annotation: The label used for the forward pagination button when the number of enumeration values, or disambiguation matches exceeds the 'Enumeration Range Size' property of the composite bag item.

systemComponent_ResolveEntities_showPrev.annotation: The label used for the backward pagination button when the number of enumeration values, or disambiguation matches exceeds the 'Enumeration Range Size' property of the composite bag item.

systemComponent_SQLIntent_noResultHeader.annotation: The header text displayed when SQL intent query returns no result.

systemComponent_SQLIntent_noResultMessag.annotation: The message displayed when SQL intent query returns no result.
The message label displayed when SQL intent query returns no result.

systemComponent_SelectCalendarEvent_acce.annotation: The text used to indicate that the invite was accepted.

systemComponent_SelectCalendarEvent_allD.annotation: The text used to indicate all-day events.

systemComponent_SelectCalendarEvent_decl.annotation: The text used to indicate that the invite was declined.

systemComponent_SelectCalendarEvent_pend.annotation: The text used to indicate that the invite status is still pending.

systemComponent_SelectCalendarEvent_prom.annotation: The text that appears before the list of meeting.

systemComponent_SelectCalendarEvent_recu.annotation: The text used to indicate recurring events.

systemComponent_SelectCalendarEvent_tent.annotation: The text used to indicate that the invite was tentatively accepted.

systemComponent_Webview_cancelLabel.annotation: The label of the cancel button to leave this state without invoking the webview.

systemComponent_Webview_linkLabel.annotation: The label of the button to invoke the webview.

systemComponent_Webview_prompt.annotation: The message for the user to tap on the link to invoke the webview.
systemComponent_Webview_prompt.message: Please tap on the link to proceed

systemConfiguration_autoNumberPrefixSepa.annotation: The separator used between the number prefix and the postback action label.

systemConfiguration_autoNumberPrefixes.annotation: The prefixes used for auto-numbering postback action labels.

systemConfiguration_conversationHistoryA.annotation: Message to display when a user clicks on a choice in the conversation history that can no longer be processed.
systemConfiguration_conversationHistoryA.message: Sorry, this choice is no longer available.

systemConfiguration_errorExpiredSessionP.annotation: The message when the session has expired.
systemConfiguration_errorExpiredSessionP.message: Your session has expired.  Please start again.

systemConfiguration_errorMaxStatesExceed.annotation: The message when the bot appears to be in an infinite loop.
systemConfiguration_errorMaxStatesExceed.message: Your session appears to be in an infinite loop.

systemConfiguration_errorUnexpectedError.annotation: The message when there is an unexpected error.
systemConfiguration_errorUnexpectedError.message: Oops I'm encountering a spot of trouble. Please try again later...

systemConfiguration_feedbackConfirmation.annotation: Confirmation message shown to the user when negative feedback has been provided.
systemConfiguration_feedbackConfirmation.message: Thank you for the feedback, I am sorry the answer was not helpful, I will try to improve!

systemConfiguration_feedbackConfirmation.annotation: Message shown to the user when positive feedback has been provided.

systemConfiguration_feedbackPrompt.annotation: Prompt used to solicit user feedback for a message shown to the user.

systemConfiguration_internalWelcomeMessa.annotation: The internal message sent to the skill when a channel handles the event that a new user has gotten access to the skill. The reply to the internal message is sent as welcome message to the new user.

systemConfiguration_oauthCancelPrompt.annotation: The message when OAuth authorization is canceled.

systemConfiguration_oauthSuccessPrompt.annotation: The message when OAuth authorization succeeds.
systemConfiguration_oauthSuccessPrompt.message: Authentication successful! You can return to the conversation.

systemConfiguration_openLinkLabel.annotation: The default label for a link.

systemConfiguration_paginationShowNext.annotation: Pagination button label to show the next set of items.

systemConfiguration_paginationStatus.annotation: Information about current set of items displayed that are part of a larger set.
